s some great hiking paths and a few of them lead to the Svartifoss waterfall. All routes are explained on the signs in the park.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Camp at the campsite provided at the Skaftafell park.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Today&#x2019;s drive: 2.5 hours<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/iceland-route-guide-cave.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"261\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"8256\" class=\"wp-image-8256 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1484px) 100vw, 1484px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave.jpg 1484w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-300x388.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-600x776.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-261x338.jpg 261w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-464x600.jpg 464w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-626x810.jpg 626w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-23x30.jpg 23w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-126x163.jpg 126w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-139x180.jpg 139w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/06\/23152741\/iceland-route-guide-cave-594x768.jpg 594w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/u